President Obama has nominated Thomas Owen Rice and Judge David Ogden Nuffer to United States District Court judgeships. Judge David Ogden Nuffer is currently a United States Magistrate Judge for the District of Utah. He has been in this position since 2003, and prior to that, he was a named partner at Snow Nuffer. His practice focused on civil litigation, real estate development, and representing local municipalities. Thomas Owen Rice currently serves as an Assistant United States Attorney for the Eastern District of Washington. He has held this position since 1987 and has served as the First Assistant United States Attorney since 2006. Rice previously worked in the Tax Division of the United States Department of Justice and was a law clerk at a law firm in 1986. Both nominees have demonstrated a commitment to justice throughout their careers.